<subSubSection id="4FEAA8A58D685D5E09E89D52C67E3BA4" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="81A95B31FCC01FC5B366B9E607A718AE" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<pageBreakToken id="E1EC6B7C34BF4592A218D31EE7D0C12B" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" start="start">Diagnosis</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8CA893A22BAB6CFC6A3D3E362B11E1B8" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
Compared to the most closely related 
<taxonomicName id="8EB06CE83E69A104E20B9FEB583F242A" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochliopidae" genus="Pyrgophorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pyrgophorus coronatus" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="coronatus">Pyrgophorus coronatus</taxonomicName>
(L. Pfeiffer, 1840), found in other cenotes and surface waters of 
<normalizedToken id="683F33CD33D6A5C968BFC0A4D68882E4" originalValue="Yucatán">Yucatan</normalizedToken>
(Figs 17-19), the new species differs by its smaller and more pyramidal shell shape with blunter apex and finer surface sculpture, whitish periorostracum, flat protoconch and less numerous whorls, more opened umbilicus, smaller and more numerous nodules and different shape of the aperture with a characteristic sinuation at its columellar edge.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="59E680CE1A16B4049211076D89E79AD8" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
Type locality. Mexico, 
<normalizedToken id="4131940CDBF3E3CB4D01ADFCE43C67E9" originalValue="Yucatán">Yucatan</normalizedToken>
state, Cenotillo Municipality, Cenote Xoch, at 46 m deep by SCUBA, buried in cave sediments, 
<geoCoordinate id="F8A029DB1666D010855B1E2F8F655217" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="20.997564">20,997565°N</geoCoordinate>
; 
<geoCoordinate id="E97D563E64126B4380992E760D69E466" direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="-87.93666">87,936659°W</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
